WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:03.003
(lively symphonic music)

00:05.106 --> 00:06.907
WOMAN: Welcome back to our
coverage of the Joshies

00:06.940 --> 00:09.577
live here on the red carpet.
Mike,

00:09.610 --> 00:11.145
Mike, can we chat
with you for a minute?

00:11.179 --> 00:12.380
- Yes.
- How are you?

00:12.413 --> 00:14.148
- How are you?
You look stunning.

00:14.182 --> 00:16.016
- The brilliant Mike Scaggs
is with me now,

00:16.050 --> 00:18.686
nominated for the award that
everyone is talking about--

00:18.719 --> 00:20.521
best man at Josh's wedding.

00:20.554 --> 00:22.423
- What is up?
(both laugh)

00:22.456 --> 00:24.525
- How are you feeling?
- Humbled.

00:24.558 --> 00:26.260
There's some great dudes
in this category.

00:26.294 --> 00:28.429
- Your friendship with Josh
has been a smash hit.

00:28.462 --> 00:30.064
How did you decide
to get involved in the project?

00:30.098 --> 00:31.232
- You know,
Josh first approached me

00:31.265 --> 00:32.400
about ten years ago.

00:32.433 --> 00:34.902
Uh, at the time,
I was at a party,

00:34.935 --> 00:36.570
slamming shots of Jager.

00:36.604 --> 00:38.906
He walked up and was like,
"Can I get in on that?"

00:38.939 --> 00:40.508
I was like, "Hell yeah, bro."

00:40.541 --> 00:42.410
- Now, you must be nervous
about tonight.

00:42.443 --> 00:44.945
- The way I see it, it's all up
to the big man upstairs...

00:44.978 --> 00:46.580
Josh.

00:46.614 --> 00:49.250
ANNOUNCER: Ladies and gentlemen,
Josh Greenberg.

00:50.818 --> 00:52.820
(orchestral flourish)

00:53.987 --> 00:57.458
- Passion, preparedness,

00:57.491 --> 00:59.360
cool to hang with--

00:59.393 --> 01:03.097
these are the qualities
of a best man.

01:03.131 --> 01:05.466
And the nominees are...

01:05.499 --> 01:07.601
Doug, "The Extra Beer."

01:09.069 --> 01:10.304
- Hey, man,
they gave me an extra beer.

01:10.338 --> 01:12.106
Want it?
- Sure.

01:21.449 --> 01:24.152
Tom, "The Lift to the Airport."

01:26.487 --> 01:28.122
- Josh?

01:28.156 --> 01:29.623
Oh, we should
probably get going.

01:29.657 --> 01:31.659
- All right.

01:33.794 --> 01:35.896
- (speaking indistinctly)

01:35.929 --> 01:38.732
- Nikhil, "The Life Saver."

01:38.766 --> 01:40.134
(dogs barking)
(yells)

01:42.470 --> 01:43.937
- Oh, my God! Look out!
(gunshot)

01:43.971 --> 01:46.574
- (distorted) No!
(dramatic music)

01:46.607 --> 01:47.908
(groans)
- Oh, my God.

01:47.941 --> 01:50.911
You saved my life.
- Of course.

01:50.944 --> 01:53.414
You're my best friend.

01:53.447 --> 01:55.883
- When did that happen?

01:57.218 --> 02:00.521
- And, finally, Mike Scaggs,

02:00.554 --> 02:02.490
"Ten Years of Friendship."

02:02.523 --> 02:05.426
(cheerful guitar music)

02:05.459 --> 02:07.161
*

02:15.503 --> 02:19.407
BOTH: Oh! Boom!

02:20.974 --> 02:23.977
(cheering, applause)
- Thank you. Stop. Stop.

02:24.011 --> 02:26.714
- And the best man goes to...

02:26.747 --> 02:28.316
Mike Scaggs,
"Ten Years of Friendship."

02:28.349 --> 02:30.551
- Come on!
Yes!

02:30.584 --> 02:32.119
- ANNOUNCER: This is the first
nomination... - What?!

02:32.152 --> 02:35.323
and first win
as best man for Mike Scaggs.

02:35.356 --> 02:36.824
- (laughing)
We did it, man!

02:36.857 --> 02:38.359
- Yeah.
- We did it!

02:38.392 --> 02:41.695
Oh, gimme this. Oh.

02:41.729 --> 02:44.465
This is for every guy
who's ever been told

02:44.498 --> 02:46.867
he is weird
for hanging out with Josh.

02:46.900 --> 02:49.703
To all those dudes,
I'm living proof.

02:49.737 --> 02:51.572
It is all worth it.
Dreams do come true.

02:51.605 --> 02:53.073
(string music plays)
Ah, no, they're playing me off.

02:53.106 --> 02:55.576
Uh, uh, okay.
Wait, um... Uh,

02:55.609 --> 02:58.246
thank you, Barry Sanderson,
Gina Gordon, Terry Stephens.

02:58.279 --> 03:00.348
We did it, Terry!
Uh, oh, shit.

03:00.381 --> 03:02.816
Oh, what... Yeah!
Uh, uh, the whales. Right.

03:02.850 --> 03:04.985
Um, every day,
four whales are killed,

03:05.018 --> 03:08.656
and that's way too many,
so, uh, you know,

03:08.689 --> 03:10.691
donate to that shit.

03:10.724 --> 03:13.527
I want to thank Cameron Crowe!
I want to thank Tom Cruise!

03:13.561 --> 03:14.662
And I want to thank Josh!

03:14.695 --> 03:17.064
He's my best friend
in the whole wide world.

03:17.097 --> 03:19.032
We've been through
everything, brother.

03:19.066 --> 03:20.834
I love you, brother.
- Okay.

03:20.868 --> 03:21.935
Okay.

03:21.969 --> 03:23.971
- Yes.
- Yeah!

03:30.143 --> 03:33.146
(downtempo electronic music)

03:34.147 --> 03:35.649
- Aah!

03:38.952 --> 03:40.954
- (squeaks)

03:42.756 --> 03:44.057
- (growls)

04:00.173 --> 04:01.775
- Dude, I still can't believe
you picked me

04:01.809 --> 04:03.110
to be your best man.
- Of course, buddy.

04:03.143 --> 04:04.445
You know me better
than anyone else.

04:04.478 --> 04:07.047
- True dat.
Ah, I'll get this.

04:07.080 --> 04:08.816
Yes, we will have
two burritos,

04:08.849 --> 04:10.818
ultra nasty
with extra drippings,

04:10.851 --> 04:12.986
butt blaster sauce,
extra blasty,

04:13.020 --> 04:14.888
and a couple
of thick-boy IPAs.

04:14.922 --> 04:18.158
- Ah, I'm-I'm trying to
cut down on the butt blasting.

04:18.191 --> 04:20.394
Uh, can I just get, like,
a... maybe a fish taco

04:20.428 --> 04:21.662
and a bottle of water?
- (cackles)

04:21.695 --> 04:22.930
Yeah, right.
Good one, bro.

04:22.963 --> 04:24.832
- Oh, my God.
- Bon apple-tits.

04:24.865 --> 04:26.734
I got food poisoning
last time I was here.

04:26.767 --> 04:27.968
Yeah, their meat is old.

04:28.001 --> 04:31.305
Got your bachelor party
all mapped out.

04:31.339 --> 04:32.406
6:00 p.m., party starts.

04:32.440 --> 04:34.742
8:00 p.m., blackout drunk.

04:34.775 --> 04:36.944
10:00 p.m.,
blackout drunk again.

04:36.977 --> 04:39.947
Midnight, party starts.

04:39.980 --> 04:41.949
What? Yeah.
- Yeah, I mean, that...

04:41.982 --> 04:44.785
- Yeah.
- That-that all sounds, uh...

04:44.818 --> 04:47.488
