(all yelling)
- Whoo-hoo!

05:23.924 --> 05:25.526
- Yeah!
- Whoo!

05:25.559 --> 05:26.827
- Feels like
it's probably got to be

05:26.860 --> 05:28.362
almost last call,
right, boys?

05:28.396 --> 05:30.498
- No way, dude.
This place is 24 hours.

05:30.531 --> 05:31.832
- It's what?
- Lock the doors

05:31.865 --> 05:33.467
and throw away the keys, baby.
- Oh, no!

05:33.501 --> 05:35.636
- Yeah!
Whoo!

05:35.669 --> 05:39.206
- Can I, uh, make a phone call?
- No problem.

05:39.239 --> 05:40.574
But, Greenberg...
- Yeah.

05:40.608 --> 05:41.909
- Be quick about it.

05:41.942 --> 05:44.912
(foreboding music)

05:44.945 --> 05:48.882
*

05:48.916 --> 05:51.685
(melancholy string music)

05:51.719 --> 05:54.822
*

05:54.855 --> 05:56.657
(door slams shut)

05:56.690 --> 05:58.692
*

05:58.726 --> 06:02.229
- How you doing?
- Uh, hanging in there.

06:02.262 --> 06:04.264
How's life on the outside?
- It's fine.

06:04.297 --> 06:06.199
Uh, I just, uh, finished
an episode of Shark Tank.

06:06.233 --> 06:08.702
This guy pitched these socks
that you can kinda draw on,

06:08.736 --> 06:10.504
so, like-like, you can,
like, customize the socks

06:10.538 --> 06:11.739
and, like, write things
on the socks--

06:11.772 --> 06:12.840
like, if you're on a team...
- (sobs)

06:12.873 --> 06:14.508
- Oh, God...

06:14.542 --> 06:16.209
I'm sorry.
Did you want me to wait?

06:16.243 --> 06:20.514
- No, no, you...
you need to live your life.

06:20.548 --> 06:22.616
From now on,
just pretend I'm dead.

06:22.650 --> 06:23.851
- Don't talk like that.

06:23.884 --> 06:25.252
- You don't know
what it's like in here.

06:25.285 --> 06:26.353
You don't know what it's like.

06:26.386 --> 06:27.555
- What's that mark on your face?

06:27.588 --> 06:29.256
Josh, did someone hurt you?

06:29.289 --> 06:33.360
- It's nothing.
- What happened, Josh?

06:33.393 --> 06:34.862
- A titty hit me in the face.

06:34.895 --> 06:36.864
- (sighs)
Oh, Josh.

06:36.897 --> 06:39.800
- I don't suppose the, uh,
governor's answered my letters.

06:39.833 --> 06:42.235
- No.
- That do-nothing son of a...

06:42.269 --> 06:45.272
- Josh... Hey, hey, hey!
Josh! Hey.

06:45.305 --> 06:46.807
(whispers) Hey, hey, hey...
- (sobbing)

06:46.840 --> 06:49.610
- You stay with me.
Stay with me, all right?

06:49.643 --> 06:51.445
Listen to me, okay?

06:51.479 --> 06:55.415
You do whatever you need to do
to get through this, all right?

06:55.449 --> 06:57.785
You do your shots,
you take your lap dances,

06:57.818 --> 06:59.887
and you come home to me,
all right?

06:59.920 --> 07:03.824
But, Josh, don't do
anything stupid, okay?

07:05.593 --> 07:08.328
- Aah!
(laughing)

07:08.361 --> 07:11.732
- Greenberg!
Uh-oh, there we go.

07:11.765 --> 07:13.133
- Yeah.
- Starting to get

07:13.166 --> 07:14.502
a little bit worried
about you, buddy.

07:14.535 --> 07:15.736
- Oh, no, I am-I am here...
(all laughing)

07:15.769 --> 07:17.805
And-and having, uh,
lots of fun.

07:17.838 --> 07:19.473
- That's what I like to hear.

07:19.507 --> 07:21.909
Bartender, give us five
of your grossest shots.

07:21.942 --> 07:23.644
We want the shit
nobody buys.

07:23.677 --> 07:26.580
(cackles)
(all laughing)

07:26.614 --> 07:28.482
Whoo!
- (cheers)

07:28.516 --> 07:29.817
- Mm.

07:29.850 --> 07:33.654
Yeah! Drink up, shitbirds.
Let's do this!

07:33.687 --> 07:36.456
Where's Josh?
- I think he went that way.

07:36.490 --> 07:38.291
- Joshie!

07:38.325 --> 07:40.494
Josh.

07:40.528 --> 07:42.863
Josh!

07:42.896 --> 07:44.698
God damn it, where is he?
(grunts)

07:44.732 --> 07:47.768
(bottle clatters into distance)

07:47.801 --> 07:50.504
*

07:50.538 --> 07:52.773
What the hell?

07:52.806 --> 07:54.808
*

08:02.550 --> 08:04.518
(whispers) No.

08:04.552 --> 08:07.721
Josh?
Josh?

08:07.755 --> 08:11.725
(roars)
Josh!

08:11.759 --> 08:14.294
- Hey, man, could we go ahead
and cut the cake?

08:14.327 --> 08:16.396
- (whispers) Whatever.
- Cool.

08:16.429 --> 08:19.567
I'll start the traditional way
by separating the two halves.

08:19.600 --> 08:22.570
(melancholy piano music)

08:22.603 --> 08:24.304
*

08:24.337 --> 08:25.338
Perfect.

08:25.372 --> 08:26.574
*

08:31.244 --> 08:34.414
- Okay, great.
Excellent.

08:34.447 --> 08:36.516
Tom will be here.
Liz will be there.

08:36.550 --> 08:38.351
The bridesmaids are here.

08:38.385 --> 08:41.254
Uh, looks like the only thing
I need now is the best man.

08:41.288 --> 08:42.990
- Yeah.
- Still no best man?

08:43.023 --> 08:46.326
- Uh, no, no, he...
he still hasn't made it yet.

08:46.359 --> 08:48.161
- Okay, so wait.
Why isn't Mike here?

08:48.195 --> 08:50.497
- Ah, you know him, he's-
he's a real party animal.

08:50.530 --> 08:51.665
He's probably just hungover.

08:51.699 --> 08:54.434
- I thought you guys quit
at, like, 10:30 last night.

08:54.467 --> 08:57.671
- I-I... I quit
at 10:30 last night.

08:57.705 --> 09:00.240
It's a possibility they might
have gone a teensy bit longer.

09:00.273 --> 09:02.409
- Josh, you bailed?
- I didn't bail.

09:02.442 --> 09:04.344
I did not bail.
- Josh. -(mouths)

09:04.377 --> 09:06.346
- Yeah, okay, they think I did.
Just, I'd like...

09:06.379 --> 09:08.248
it's not a big deal.
I left a bit early.

09:08.281 --> 09:09.883
Who cares about
some stupid party?

09:09.917 --> 09:11.418
- Who wants to see
the bachelorette party pictures?

09:11.451 --> 09:12.953
- Oh, my God, me, me,
me, me, me. - Oh, my God,

09:12.986 --> 09:14.955
that was the craziest night
we've ever had.

09:14.988 --> 09:16.189
- But also the most important.

09:16.223 --> 09:18.191
- It cemented
our friendship forever.

09:18.225 --> 09:19.860
- Guys, I feel
the exact same way.

09:19.893 --> 09:21.361
- I know we made you do
a few things

09:21.394 --> 09:23.030
that made you uncomfortable.
- But you stuck it out.

09:23.063 --> 09:25.365
- And the significance of that
was not lost on us.

09:25.398 --> 09:26.767
- Yeah, I feel like
this conversation

09:26.800 --> 09:28.401
could probably happen
some other time.

09:28.435 --> 09:30.203
- Lucy, we love you.
And because of that night

09:30.237 --> 09:31.471
and, like, how long
you stayed...

09:31.504 --> 09:33.874
- Oh, for (bleep) sake.
- ...we always will.

09:33.907 --> 09:35.876
- Aw.
You guys, I love you too.

09:35.909 --> 09:38.311
- (squeals cheerfully)
- (giggles)

09:38.345 --> 09:39.546
- (whimpering)

09:39.579 --> 09:41.882
- Okay, I get it.
I'm sorry.

09:41.915 --> 09:43.416
I'm sorry I left early.

09:43.450 --> 09:45.385
But it's not a big deal.

09:45.418 --> 09:46.754
Mike doesn't hold grudges.

09:46.787 --> 09:48.789
(eerie string music)

10:08.942 --> 10:10.243
- Aah!

10:10.277 --> 10:12.012
(dramatic orchestral music)

10:30.798 --> 10:32.632
(ominous musical flourish)

10:32.666 --> 10:34.935
- All right, Nana,
there you are.

10:34.968 --> 10:37.337
You're all set.
- Joshie.

10:37.370 --> 10:39.339
Joshie, we may have
a teensy little issue.

10:39.372 --> 10:42.109
- What?
- Mike is finally here.

10:42.142 --> 10:44.144
But while we have
a seat for him,

10:44.177 --> 10:45.512
we don't have any
for his henchmen.

10:45.545 --> 10:47.147
- For his-his henchmen?
What?

10:47.180 --> 10:50.483
- (cackling)

10:50.517 --> 10:52.152
(sinister music)

10:52.185 --> 10:54.321
Okay, boys, it's showtime!

10:54.354 --> 10:56.356
- Go get him, boss.
- Yeah! Show him.

10:56.389 --> 10:57.624
- Who the (bleep)
are these guys?

10:57.657 --> 10:59.159
Mike, are you...
are you all right?

10:59.192 --> 11:00.961
- Never better, Joshie boy.

11:00.994 --> 11:03.864
Sorry to crash
your little party.

11:03.897 --> 11:05.398
- Well, you didn't crash it.
You were invited.

11:05.432 --> 11:07.134
It's... You're the best man.
This is a wedding rehearsal.

11:07.167 --> 11:09.169
- (cackling)
- What are you...

11:09.202 --> 11:12.205
- Ah, champagne.
Don't mind if I...

11:12.239 --> 11:13.907
don't!

11:13.941 --> 11:15.876
That's kinda wasteful.
- (cackles)

11:15.909 --> 11:17.377
(screeching)

11:17.410 --> 11:19.880
- Can you please just calm down?
- Oh, I wish I could,

11:19.913 --> 11:21.081
but...
(sniffs)

11:21.114 --> 11:22.115
something's burning.

11:24.517 --> 11:27.320
(chuckles)
Toasts.

11:27.354 --> 11:31.825
- "A" is for "amour,"
which Josh and Lucy truly feel.

11:31.859 --> 11:33.493
"B" is for "belonging."

11:33.526 --> 11:36.029
- That's right.
As soon as Liz is done,

11:36.063 --> 11:38.832
my toast is gonna blow
this place sky high.

11:38.866 --> 11:41.201
- (laughs) Yeah.
Clock's ticking, idiot.

11:41.234 --> 11:43.503
- Who are you?
- "E" is for "embark."

11:43.536 --> 11:46.006
Their new journey has begun.
-I'm pretty sure our e-mail said

11:46.039 --> 11:48.241
we have to keep the speeches
between three and five minutes.

11:48.275 --> 11:51.511
- Length is the least of
your worries, Joshie boy.

11:51.544 --> 11:53.346
This card's about
your herpes scare.

11:53.380 --> 11:55.082
- Oh, my God.
- This card's about ISIS.

11:55.115 --> 11:56.583
- Why?
