that shit anymore.

12:19.072 --> 12:20.874
- Yeah, or is it that you
just don't like me anymore?

12:20.908 --> 12:22.475
- Why are you so
hung up on this?

12:22.509 --> 12:23.977
It was just a party.

12:24.011 --> 12:26.213
- No, it wasn't
just a party, man.

12:26.246 --> 12:27.881
It was our last chance
to hang out,

12:27.915 --> 12:30.050
and you left without
even saying good-bye.

12:30.083 --> 12:31.885
- (sighs)
- And finally "Z."

12:31.919 --> 12:35.322
"Z" is for "Zarathustra,"

12:35.355 --> 12:37.457
which I think speaks for itself.

12:37.490 --> 12:39.059
(scattered applause)

12:39.092 --> 12:40.928
- Are there any other toasts?

12:40.961 --> 12:44.397
- Please...

12:44.431 --> 12:45.966
- Don't worry.

12:45.999 --> 12:47.801
I'm not gonna ruin
any more of your life.

12:47.835 --> 12:50.804
- I...
(sighs) Mike...

12:50.838 --> 12:54.842
Mike, can I talk to you
without your neon beatniks?

12:54.875 --> 12:56.309
Mike?

13:00.047 --> 13:02.782
- (sighs) Hi.
Mike, it's me, uh, again.

13:02.816 --> 13:05.618
I'm-I'm really,
really sorry, man.

13:05.652 --> 13:07.520
I mean it.
I'm-I'm sorry.

13:07.554 --> 13:09.122
Just please call me back,
please.

13:10.490 --> 13:11.791
(sighs)
- Hey.

13:11.825 --> 13:13.360
- Hi.
- Any luck?

13:13.393 --> 13:15.963
- Uh, no, no, I think
he's still pretty upset.

13:15.996 --> 13:17.865
- Well, you know what?
I'm sure he is,

13:17.898 --> 13:20.100
but just give him
some time, okay?

13:20.133 --> 13:22.502
He's gonna forgive you.
You're his best friend.

13:22.535 --> 13:24.972
(dramatic music)

13:25.005 --> 13:26.874
- MIKE:
After much consideration,

13:26.907 --> 13:29.977
I have decided to retire
as Josh's best friend.

13:30.010 --> 13:31.979
- Mike, how can you
just walk away?

13:32.012 --> 13:34.047
You're the greatest ever,
and you're still in your prime.

13:34.081 --> 13:35.282
- Had a great career,
you know,

13:35.315 --> 13:36.884
set a lot
of best friend records--

13:36.917 --> 13:38.318
most consecutive hangs,

13:38.351 --> 13:40.820
also grossest bare-ass fart
to Josh's face.

13:40.854 --> 13:42.990
It's one I believe
may never be broken.

13:43.023 --> 13:45.192
Uh, but there's more to life
than being Josh's best friend.

13:45.225 --> 13:47.160
Yeah, I want to spend time
with my family,

13:47.194 --> 13:49.162
explore some
business opportunities,

13:49.196 --> 13:51.965
and also pursue
my other lifelong dream.

13:51.999 --> 13:54.667
- What dream?
- To play professional baseball.

13:54.701 --> 13:56.169
(all gasping and murmuring)

13:56.203 --> 13:58.038
I am thrilled to announce
that I have just signed

13:58.071 --> 13:59.907
a minor league,
non-guaranteed contract

13:59.940 --> 14:01.641
with the Chattanooga Mud Dogs.

14:01.674 --> 14:04.144
With any luck, I will accomplish
just as much in baseball

14:04.177 --> 14:05.678
as I did being
Josh's best friend.

14:05.712 --> 14:07.014
Thank you.
ALL: Michael!

14:07.047 --> 14:09.016
- Thank you, Mikey.
-JOSH: What?

14:09.049 --> 14:10.650
- I didn't know
Mike played baseball.

14:10.683 --> 14:13.053
- I mean, he played softball
at middle school,

14:13.086 --> 14:14.754
and he was terrible.

14:14.787 --> 14:17.991
Okay, um...
Uh, Lucy, I know

14:18.025 --> 14:19.192
we still have, like,
wedding stuff to do, but...

14:19.226 --> 14:22.262
- Josh, Josh,
this is important, okay?

14:22.295 --> 14:25.198
(bright acoustic guitar music)

14:25.232 --> 14:28.068
Go to Chattanooga.
- (whispers) Yeah.

14:28.101 --> 14:29.836
(both sigh)

14:29.869 --> 14:32.072
- I love you!

14:32.105 --> 14:34.107
*

14:47.254 --> 14:49.856
- Okay, hustle up, y'all!

14:49.889 --> 14:51.224
Let's practice.

14:51.258 --> 14:53.393
Practice makes perfect,
right?

14:53.426 --> 14:55.595
Ah, love me some drills,
right, baby?

14:55.628 --> 14:57.430
(pastoral music)

14:57.464 --> 14:59.632
Doing a no-hitter today,
right?

14:59.666 --> 15:01.701
Come on, come on.
Hit me! Come on.

15:01.734 --> 15:03.536
Come on. Aah!

15:03.570 --> 15:05.438
(groans)

15:05.472 --> 15:08.308
- Mike! Mike!
Can you sign this?

15:08.341 --> 15:10.310
- Sure, kid, what do you got?
A baseball poster?

15:10.343 --> 15:13.113
- Nah, it's from your old days
as Josh's best friend.

15:13.146 --> 15:14.581
- That was a good year.

15:14.614 --> 15:17.617
Sorry, kid,
I don't do that anymore.

15:17.650 --> 15:20.253
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I need to do batting.

15:23.490 --> 15:26.426
All right, Guerrero,
don't hold back!

15:26.459 --> 15:28.295
(grunts)
(clapping)

15:28.328 --> 15:30.730
- Yeah, nice--nice swing.

15:30.763 --> 15:34.067
- What do you want?
- Just want to apologize, man.

15:34.101 --> 15:36.803
- Nothing to be sorry for, man.
It's better this way.

15:36.836 --> 15:39.572
We're both doing exactly
what we were born to do.

15:39.606 --> 15:43.176
You're marrying Lucy,
and I'm playing baseball.

15:44.277 --> 15:46.079
-MAN: Oh!

15:46.113 --> 15:47.680
- Uh, I've probably done
enough batting.

15:49.516 --> 15:53.353
- Mike, I-I totally
believe you have

15:53.386 --> 15:56.123
exactly what it takes to be
a professional baseball player.

15:56.156 --> 15:58.992
- Obviously.
- But I need you on my team.

15:59.026 --> 16:01.694
- Dude, you don't, okay?
You're a full grown-up now.

16:01.728 --> 16:03.863
It's like I don't even know
how to be your friend anymore.

16:03.896 --> 16:05.498
*

16:05.532 --> 16:08.368
- Hey, you remember-
remember freshman year

16:08.401 --> 16:12.272
when you and I would each pound,
like, 12 beers a night?

16:12.305 --> 16:14.341
- Yeah, that was great.
- It-it was.

16:14.374 --> 16:15.775
Uh, and then I was like,

16:15.808 --> 16:17.444
"I don't think
I can do this anymore.

16:17.477 --> 16:19.479
I'm literally gonna die
from alcohol poisoning."

16:19.512 --> 16:22.715
It was the end of an era,
but it wasn't the end of us.

16:22.749 --> 16:25.652
Why? Because you
came up with the idea

16:25.685 --> 16:28.655
of smoking pot every day.
- That's right.

16:28.688 --> 16:31.058
God, it was hard
at first. Scary.

16:31.091 --> 16:35.028
- But we stuck with it,
and we eventually leveled out.

16:35.062 --> 16:38.631
And-and if we can go through
a huge change like that,

16:38.665 --> 16:41.501
what can't we deal with?

16:41.534 --> 16:44.204
- You came all the way
to Chattanooga to tell me that?

16:44.237 --> 16:45.572
- Yup.
- Wait.

16:45.605 --> 16:48.508
Aren't you worried
about missing the wedding?

16:48.541 --> 16:50.443
- No wedding
without my best man.

16:55.082 --> 16:57.550
- Well, Coach,
it's been a crazy ride.

16:57.584 --> 17:00.019
It's no secret we didn't
always see eye to eye,

17:00.053 --> 17:02.389
but even though I'm leaving
the clubhouse today

17:02.422 --> 17:04.557
and I won't be there
for the doubleheader

17:04.591 --> 17:07.160
against the Water Bears
and the Sky Grizzlies,

17:07.194 --> 17:10.397
I want you to know I will always
consider Chattanooga my home,

17:10.430 --> 17:14.401
and I will always,
always bleed Mud Dog blue.

17:14.434 --> 17:17.237
So I guess what
I'm trying to say is...

17:17.270 --> 17:18.571
- You're out.

17:18.605 --> 17:20.107
(indistinct chatter)

17:20.140 --> 17:22.075
BOTH: Hey!

17:22.109 --> 17:24.177
(both laughing)
- Ah, they're gonna miss me.

17:24.211 --> 17:25.412
- Yeah, for sure.
I know I do.

17:25.445 --> 17:27.580
- Yeah, hey,
I miss you too, buddy.

17:27.614 --> 17:29.682
-MAN:
Oh! The same spot!

17:29.716 --> 17:31.584
- Yeah.

17:31.618 --> 17:35.422
(bright acoustic guitar music)

17:35.455 --> 17:37.023
Pound it.
(laughs)

17:37.056 --> 17:38.625
- Wow, cool,
there's a poster of us?

17:38.658 --> 17:40.627
- Yeah, man.
You want one?

17:40.660 --> 17:42.429
- I'd love one.
- Hey, you know,

17:42.462 --> 17:44.631
I'm making a movie
with Bugs Bunny...

17:48.301 --> 17:51.070
- Uh, okay, excellent.
So Tom will be there,

17:51.104 --> 17:53.440
Liz will be there,
and then, uh, the best man,

17:53.473 --> 17:57.410
my best man, will be
on that spot right there.

17:57.444 --> 17:59.246
- Uh, w-what if
I don't hit my spot?

17:59.279 --> 18:00.913
Does it have to be exact or...
- Nah.

18:00.947 --> 18:02.549
Just kinda know
your general area.

18:02.582 --> 18:04.417
- Right, right,
right, got you.

18:04.451 --> 18:06.286
- Uh, and then the music begins,
you'll walk down the aisle

18:06.319 --> 18:07.787
at a slightly
slower-than-normal pace.

18:07.820 --> 18:10.056
- Okay, like this?
- Eh, no.

18:10.089 --> 18:11.791
No, no. Slow-slower
than normal--

18:11.824 --> 18:13.993
um, deliberate.
- Ah, shit, bro,

18:14.026 --> 18:16.062
what if I blow it?
- Mike, you're gonna do great.

18:16.095 --> 18:17.797
- (sighs)
- Here, take my arm...

18:17.830 --> 18:19.432
- Okay.
- We'll do it together.

18:19.466 --> 18:21.501
(gentle acoustic guitar music)
BOTH: Hm.

18:21.534 --> 18:23.002
- * Ooh *

18:23.035 --> 18:24.070
- Hey, I've been
meaning to ask you,

18:24.103 --> 18:25.405
when did Nikhil get shot?

18:25.438 --> 18:26.639
- Oh, I never told you
that story?

18:26.673 --> 18:27.940
- No!
- Okay.

18:27.974 --> 18:29.776
- So last month
in Caracas...

18:29.809 --> 18:33.346
* - I saw a name
in the graveyard that I knew *

18:33.380 --> 18:37.250
* Glowing like the neon
in a lounge light *

18:37.284 --> 18:40.620
* I picked away all
the gray hairs that I'd grown *

18:40.653 --> 18:43.623
* That remained
on the outside *

18:45.358 --> 18:49.262
* And I'm wound tight *

18:49.296 --> 18:53.032
* And bound by
the secrets you saved *

18:53.065 --> 18:55.134
* The pieces you kept *

18:55.168 --> 18:58.037
* They've risen and slept
without you *

